  "texts": [
    "Figure 1 shows a comparison of ELMo, OpenAI GPT, and BERT.",
    "Improvements to and Extensions of Pretrained Language ModelsThe advantage of BERT's auto-encoding language model is that it can use contextualized information on the given word to better predict its vector representation.",
    "Because BERT has pioneered a new area of NLP, many variants and extensions based on it have emerged.Yang et al. introduced XLNET [155] in 2019.",
    "It is an auto-regressive language model based on Transformer-XL [146],in which all tokens are predicted in random order, rather than sequentially, and the joint probability of each predicted token is factorized by using the product rule to address the issue of a discrepancy between pretraining and fine-tuning in BERT due to the use of artificial symbols like [MASK].",
    "In addition, XLNET incorporates the advantages of the auto-encoding language model, and obtains contextualized information by introducing the permutation language model and two-stream self-attention."
  ],
